Monokuma | Kev 2021-10-29 00:31:20Z
The interior lake reveals odd parts of geographical formation on this island. Despite the island being covered by ocean water on all sides, the center of the island contains a fairly large lake. This means that the island as a whole is shaped like a ring. However, that isn't what catches your eye here. The giant stone spear in the center... On top of that, a whirlpool encompasses much of the pool, making it rather dangerous to swim inside it. Attempting to touch the spear... Well, I'm not sure you would want to do that. The whirlpool is moving rather fast too, sucking any and all objects directly into the center of the lake where the spear sits, making the whole scene similar to a giant blender of sorts. Moments like this don't last forever. Just being here radiates a sense of urgency. Wildlife seems to avoid the lake, and even the water seems rather foreign. However, touching and drinking the water seems perfectly safe. A rainbow even forms over the lake due to the mist being kicked up by the whirlpool. The scene is peaceful, but filled with a sense of terror.
